Actually, I think there is some sort of option to turn off images/signatures for you in ezBoard.  If not, you can always turn off images in your browser. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubiggins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Biggins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/29/01 3:09:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1480.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Really big signatures...</span><hr size=1> The Safehouse limits total signature size to 15k. That includes all personal icons (those little thingies by your user name on the left). That rule seems to work pretty good. It's up to the mods to watch for the big sigs and edit them out, though. <p><img src="http://www27.brinkster.com/jtemple/horserat.jpg"><br><FONT SIZE=+1><a href=http://casusbelli.tamu.edu/magelo.php?mid=13102><B>Biggins Black: Assassin</B></a></FONT><BR>
