<br>
But you are right that people should be thinking about the size of their signature picture before posting all over, and this comes from someone with DSL and no problems reading any image heavy board <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubiggins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Biggins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/30/01 12:45:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1480.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Really big signatures...</span><hr size=1> Personally, I like the one sig per thread rule. What's the point in seeing someone's giant sig pic 15 times in one thread? Especially if they only post a sentence or two each time. It turns into a thread of 15 sig pics instead of actual readable content.<br>
<br>
Also, people should resize a pic to fit their needs before making it part of their sig or personal icon thing. There's nothing more annoying than seeing a 1 x 1 cm picture that's a 1 megabyte download. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uulvrim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ulvrim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/30/01 2:59:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1480.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Really big signatures...</span><hr size=1> Question: Why signatures at all?<br>
1. They take a while to download.<br>
2. They aren't really a essential function of a forum (at least in my opinion a forum is for communication and sure a pic says more than a  1000 words, but 2 identical pics still just say those 1000 words. I'm sure that if I had been more literate and stuff I could have said this better, but I hope you catch my drift).<br>
3. You can post whatever pictures you want somewhere else and link 'em. <br>
4. You can have all your cool qoutes in simple text.<br>
5. You can have a big enough picture under your name to the right.<br>
6. I'm on a 33.6 modem with a gfx card that cant handle more than 800x600.<br>
7. I'm pretty sure that if the browser has loaded a pic once it will have it stored in the cache and therefore won't have to load it again. At least as long as it's not bigger than something something size.<br>
8. And if you MUST have a signature with a pic, please make it wider than it is tall... For example the standard banner-size ratio. At least I think this is better than having a big square. It looks nicer.<br>
<br>
So, now I've ventured an opinion on ayonae-ro boards for the first time. Feel free to flame me to death! :P<br>
